# adding some checks inside the schema or DB
- adding diffrent schemaTypes
- eg - required, unique, default, trim, lowercase, minLength, maxLength ... - this checks let database not to pollute
- min & max - use for a number
- minLength & maxLength - use for string
- custome - validate function

  validate(value){
            if(!["male", "female", "others"].includes(value)){
                throw new Error("Gender data is not valid !");
            }
        }
@ Note - this validate function is only applicable, if new user is created, it will not applicable in patch(update method)
       - so, to apply in update (patch method) we are using "runValidators"




